args:
Nedrick makes contact with the Dawnshard and
escapes to a world that represents his own past.
When Zethia pursues him, the two begin to
battle, with Bahamut's pact as the prize.
Meanwhile, the prince and his allies are forced
to stand against an onslaught of fiends.
Use the power I have given you,\nand I will use you all.
Rebel against this world. Shake it free of\nits reverie. You shall be called...Agito.
(This is another world—something akin\nto my past, and yet not.)
(It seems I have successfully opened a\nchannel with the Dawnshard—but this is\nonly the beginning.)
(Now I will leap into the past I have to\nchange—and alter it!)
(This right here... This is the moment\nI must change.)

(That is me when I was on the cusp of
succumbing to wyrmscale. It is time to
give that version of me the power which
I now possess.)
(I will then link this world to the one\nwhere my body still resides.)
(I learned the means to do so during my\njourney with Jin. And with this ability,\nI can alter causality.)
Then Bahamut and I can forge a new\npact—a PROPER pact!
What happened? Nedrick collapsed the\nmoment he touched the Dawnshard.
He has escaped to another world.\nHe will alter the past—and correct it—\nbefore returning to this world once more.
The past cannot be altered!\nIt's impossible!
The closest thing one might be able to do\nis use the Dawnshard to reach a world that\nis in the same state as that of our past.
But his actions there would mean nothing\nin THIS world!

And while actions in that world might
produce new possibilities that branch off
into manifold paths, that is all. He can do
no more.
If it were to become possible to rewrite\nthe past, it would change the very nature\nof our world's existence!
And yet, that is exactly what he will do.\nI know this because he gained the means\nto do so while on his journey with me.
All this time, he has carried on with the\nresolve to change the way of our world.
This resolve is absolute—unlike the lot of\nyou, who totter about from one ideal to\nthe next with the winds!
...I'm going to follow Nedrick to this other\nworld and stop him.
Are you sure? There's no telling what you\nmight lose in the process.
Then I'll support you with all my power.\nStop Nedrick, Zethia. Please.
What did you mean when you said Zethia\ncould lose something?
Whatever it is, this is a dangerous idea.\nI can't let you do it!
Do not look to stop me, Brother.\nInstead, bear witness to my resolve!
And what do you think you will do?
I am an Auspex. With my mana, I should\nbe able to make my way to the world that\nNedrick is attempting to change.
Once there, I will stop him!
You assume I will permit you to pass?
That sounds like our cue. Time to stop\nthis faerie, {player_name}!

Look, I get that you're worried, but Zethia
isn't some bauble for you to keep safe.
She can make choices for herself and
move forward of her own volition.
You're her brother. Would you really stand\nin the way of her doing so?
Rather than hold her back, you should\nsupport whatever choice she makes.
AM I her brother though? I mean, I just\nfound out we're not related by blood,\nso what does that even make us?

Blood's got nothing to do with it. Parent
and child, brother and sister—whatever
the relationship, all that matters is that
your hearts are one.
The strength of a bond is something you\nshould know very, very well. Right?
...You're right. We have to help her.
Now, Zethia! Run! Make contact with the\nDawnshard and escape to the past!
Hrk... One thing after the other!
(Nedrick faced down our attacks without\nhesitation and made for the Dawnshard.)
(He does not fear death in the slightest\nwhen it comes to fulfilling his ideals.\nI am...impressed.)
(And now that he has whisked himself to\nthe past, the only one who can prevent\nhis pact is Zethia.)
(If she manages to do so, that would be\nexcellent news for me, but who knows\nhow that will go...)
What should I do, Phares? Pour in even more\nblack mana and crush them all?
No. We'll buy time until he arrives.
The alteration is complete, and this world\nand mine are now connected.
If I return to my original world now, I will\nhave my complete pact with Bahamut.
That will not come to pass, Nedrick!
Ah, I see. You used the Dawnshard to\nbecome a spirit mana projection and\npursued me to this place.
Sadly, you are too late. I have already\ncompleted my pact with Bahamut.
No. There is still a means open to me.
With this blade entrusted to me by Ilia,\nI will claim the pact made between\nyou and Bahamut.
Dragonblood flows within my veins.\nThere should be no reason I cannot.
Do you truly think you can steal a pact\nand emerge unscathed?
To say nothing of the fact that we speak of\nno ordinary dragon. Bahamut is a creature\nof immense and terrible power.
To twist a pact that has already been\nmade goes against the very nature of\nthings—and could well cost you your life.
For the sake of a future teeming with\npossibility, I will stop you at any cost!
She has crossed over to another world.\nAll we can do now is...
Zethia's fighting in her world, so we'll\ndefend her to the death in this one!
